Ask HN: Adversarial AI for Job Applications
text:
Is there an adversarial model for resume screeners?

I'm pretty tired of trying to figure out whatever the correct number of keywords is, or what the trendy buzzwords are. I imagine this as like a triplet loss problem for JDs, resumes, and screening passes.

Show HN: Monitor meta tag issues and automate indexing on Google
text:
Hi HN,

My name is Chris, I have been building https://tagparrot.com as a solution for two primary SEO purposes:

1) Easy way to visually review all your pages title, description and image tags in one go, get notified when there are issues.

2) Automate the process of requesting indexing to Google for all of your pages.

No longer need to wait for every page to be indexed or manually submit individual URL's one at a time, we can take care of it all in the background.

Thanks

Ask HN: Seeking a Co-Founder for SurTax, a Commercial Property Services Company
text:
Hi Hacker News community,

I'm currently running a business called SurTax, a services company that focuses on helping commercial property owners save money on their taxes by identifying potential refunds on Direct Assessments and Special Assessments. We have access to the most precise data available to determine which properties can benefit from our services, and we've already laid the groundwork for significant success.

The commercial property tax refund market has huge potential, with our competitors refunding around $20 million a year collectively. However, there's still approximately $40 million a year in untapped refunds, and I believe SurTax can capture a significant portion of this market with the right strategy and execution.

As the founder, I bring extensive data analysis and industry expertise to the table. However, I recognize that my strengths lie in the technical side of the business, and I need a partner who can complement my skills and help drive SurTax's growth.

I'm looking for a co-founder who can help with: - Sales strategy: Identifying the most effective sales channels and methods for targeting commercial property owners. - Marketing and copywriting: Crafting compelling messaging that effectively communicates the value of our services and drives customer acquisition. - Design and branding: Ensuring that our visual identity is professional, consistent, and appealing to our target audience.

If you have experience in sales, marketing, or design, and are passionate about helping businesses grow and succeed, I'd love to discuss the opportunity to work together on SurTax.

Please feel free to reach out to me via founding (at) surtax.llc if you're interested in learning more about the business, the market potential, and how we can join forces to capture the untapped potential in the commercial property tax refund space.

Looking forward to hearing from you!
